{{Expand Azerbaijani|Fransa azərbaycanlıları|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox ethnic group | group = Azerbaijanis in France | population = '''1.112''' (asylum-seekers),<ref>[http://www.enpi-info.eu/.../Azerbaijan_Profile2008.pdf ]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> '''70,000''' Estimate<ref>http://az.trend.az/news/society/1034370.html#popupInfo</ref> | popplace = [[Paris]], [[Alsace]], [[Bordeaux]], [[Marseille]] | langs = [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]], [[French language|French]], [[Turkish language|Turkish]], [[Persian language|Persian]] | religions = [[Shia Islam]] }} {{Azerbaijanis}}
'''Azerbaijanis in France''' ({{lang-az|Fransa azərbaycanlıları}}) is a small [[Azerbaijani diaspora]] in [[France]], are [[France|French]] citizens and permanent residents of ethnic [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijani]] background. Most Azerbaijani-France have immigrated to France from the [[Republic of Azerbaijan]] and [[Iran]].
== History == The migrations of Azerbaijanis to France began in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. They are mostly [[asylum-seekers]] or [[political refugees]], who came to France following the [[Iranian Revolution]] in 1979.{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}
Strengthening of France's position in Europe has accelerated the migration of the Azerbaijanis to this country since the end of the 19th century. Azerbaijani millionaires such as Haji Zeynalabdin Tagiyev, Musa Nagiyev, Shamsi Asadullayev and French businessmen created business together in France.
After the decline of the [[Azerbaijan Democratic Republic]], [[France]] was one of the 10 countries where Azerbaijani migrants settled. Famous Azerbaijanis such as [[Alimardan Topchubashov]], [[Ali bey Huseynzade]], [[Jeyhun Hajibeyli]], Umbulbanin settled in France.
After the declaration of independence of Azerbaijan in 1991, the establishment of bilateral relations between France and Azerbaijan affected the activities of the Azerbaijani diaspora. The books "Karabagh history and the present period", "Karabagh" (collection of articles), "Nagorno-Karabagh", "History of [[Nagorno-Karabakh]] and its documents" were published in France.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.azerbaijans.com/content_495_en.html|title=Diaspora organizations in abroad|last=|first=|date=|website=www.azerbaijans.com|language=az|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>
== The Azerbaijani-French Youth Association (AFYA) == The Azerbaijani-French Youth Association (AFYA) was established in 2003 by a group of Azerbaijani students studying in [[Paris]]. The first president of the association was Babek Ismailov, who studied in Paris at that time. In the following years, Mirvari Fataliyeva was the head of the organization. More than 50 AFYA members are Azerbaijanis, French and foreigners living in France. The main purpose of AFYA is to strengthen friendly relations between Azerbaijan and France, as well as to support the development of economic, scientific and cultural relations, along with sharing information about Azerbaijani culture, history, successes and even problems. The organization carries out activities and projects in Paris, as well as in different cities of France. Chairman of Azerbaijani-French Youth Association is Vusala Mammadzadeh.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/AZERBAIJANS_MUSICIANS_ATTEND_BERLIOZ_FESTIVAL-564107|title=AZERBAIJAN'S MUSICIANS ATTEND BERLIOZ FESTIVAL|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en}}</ref>
== The Azerbaijan Cultural Center == The Azerbaijan Cultural Center has been operated in Strasbourg since 1990. The aim of the Cultural Center is to serve protection of the culture and folklore of Azerbaijani people by organizing cultural events and national holidays. Chairman of the Azerbaijan Cultural Center is Ahmed Mehribani.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://heydar-aliyev-foundation.org/en/content/view/136/2178/The-Azerbaijan-Cultural-Centre-in-Paris|title=The Azerbaijan Cultural Centre in Paris|website=heydar-aliyev-foundation.org|language=en|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>
== The Society of Azerbaijani Students of France == The Society of Azerbaijani Students of France (SASF) was established in 1999 in Strasbourg. The main principles of the Association are to bring together Azerbaijani students studying and graduating in France, to demonstrate the truth about Azerbaijan, January 20, Khojaly tragedy, March 31, the Genocide of Azerbaijanis both to the French public and to the whole world. The Association prepares programs and articles about Azerbaijan and its problems on radio and television channels as well as web pages. Chairman of the Azerbaijani Students Association in France is Mammad Ismayilov.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://diaspora.gov.az/index.php?options=content&id=660|title=Diasporla İş üzrə Dövlət Komitəsi/State Committee for Work with Diaspora|last=|first=|date=|website=diaspora.gov.az|language=az|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>
== Strasbourg "Azerbaijan House" == "Azerbaijani House" was founded in May 2005 in Strasbourg. The aim of the Strasbourg "Azerbaijani House", which combines 3 communities the Society of Cultural Relations with Azerbaijan, the Azerbaijan Cultural Center, the Society of Azerbaijani Students is to bring together Azerbaijanis living in the region, to help operate as a united diaspora and to promote the history, culture and art of Azerbaijan, to show the truth about it to the local community. The society has been operated in the center of Strasbourg and 500 meters from the Council of Europe since February 16, 2007. Chairman of the "Azerbaijani House" Society is Mustafa Alinca.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azertag.az/xeber/STRASBURQDA_AZARBAYCAN_EVI_YARADILMISDIR-356315|title="AZERBAIJAN HOUSE" IN STRASBOURG was created.|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=az|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vazehasgarov.blogspot.com/2013/01/irene-melikoff-lazerbaidjan-sovietique.html|title=VAZEH|last=ASGAROV|first=Publié par Vazeh|language=fr|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/AZERBAIJAN_HOUSE_IN_STRASBOURG_TO_MARK_15TH_ANNIVERSARY_OF_SHUSHAS_OCCUPATION-566303|title=AZERBAIJAN HOUSE IN STRASBOURG TO MARK 15TH ANNIVERSARY OF SHUSHA'S OCCUPATION|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/PROTEST_RALLY_TO_BE_HELD_IN_STRASBOURG_TO_MARK_16th_ANNIVERSARY_OF_KHOJALY_GENOCIDE-572575|title=PROTEST RALLY TO BE HELD IN STRASBOURG TO MARK 16th ANNIVERSARY OF KHOJALY GENOCIDE|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/RADIOBROADCAST_ON_AZERBAIJAN_REALITIES_AIRED_IN_STRASBOURG-563453|title=RADIOBROADCAST ON AZERBAIJAN REALITIES AIRED IN STRASBOURG|access-date=2018-04-12|language=en}}</ref> ==Notable people== {{further information|:Category:French people of Azerbaijani descent}}
